                <h3>Nutrition Monitoring (Football Training and Matches)</h3>
                <p>
                	As well as good nutrition on the day itself, it is recommended that 
                	you have a higher than normal carbohydrate intake at all meals, after 
                	training on the day prior to the match. The plan below provides sufficient
                	levels of all nutrients and sustained slow released low glycaemic 
                	carbohydrates to ensure optimal energy throughout two 45 minute half-times
                	in a game of football. It also encourages good nutrition after the game,
                	to ensure you're refuelled for training the next week.

                </p>
                <p><a href="nutrition.jsp"><b>Back to Nutrition Page</b></a>
                <p><b>Football Match Nutrition</b></p>
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Breakfast 7.30am:</b>
                    	<br>
                    	<ul>
	                    	<li>
	                    	Large bowl of porridge oats made with jumbo oats, 
	                    	+ 200ml of skimmed milk,
	                    	+ water with a tea spoon of suger and raisens if desired,
	                    	<br>
	                    	<br>	
	                    	or
	                    	<br>
	                    	<br>
	                    	</li>
	                    	
	                    	<li>
	                    	75g of unsweetened muesli + 250ml of skimmed milk,
	                    	250ml of fresh fruit juice,
	                    	Tea/Coffee
	                    	</li>
                    	</ul>
                    	<br>			
                    </li>
                    
                    <li><b>10.00 am:</b>
                    	<ul>
                    		<li>2-3 oatcakes with low fat soft cheese</li>
                    		<li>Item of fruit(Banana)</li>
                    		<li>Drink</li>
                    	</ul>
                    	<br>
                    </li>
                    <li><b>Early Lunch 12.00pm:</b>
                    	<ul>
                    		<li>100g chicken breast or 120g fish</li>
                    		<li>70g basmati rice or 70g wholewheat pasta</li>
                    		<li>Medium serving of vegetables / salad</li>
                    		<li>Drink Water</li>
                    	</ul>
                    	<br>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                    <b>15 minutes before kick-off / throw-in:</b>
                    	<ul>
                    		<li>1-2 oatcakes</li>
                    		<li>100ml of isotonic drink with 20g of additional dextrose</li>
                    	</ul>
                    	<br>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                    <b>Half time:</b>
                    	<ul>
                    		<li>100ml of isotonic drink with 20g of additional dextrose</li>
                    		<li>Drink water</li>
                    	</ul>
                    	<br>
                    </li>
                    <li><b>Immediately after match:</b>
                    	<ul>
                    		<li>25g of whey protein + 25g of dextrose in water</li>
                    	</ul>
                    	<br>
                    </li>
                    <li><b>45 minutes later - main meal:</b>
                    	<ul>
                    		<li>Lean fillet steak or chicken breast or fish or herbs to taste<br>
                    			Boiled new potatoes or basmati or dry roasted sweet potatoes<br>
                    			Loads of mixed vegetables<br>
                    			Low fat, no added suger yoghurt<br>
                    			Drink</li>
                    	</ul>
                    	<br>
                    </li>
                    <li><b>Evening snack:</b>
                    	<ul>
                    		<li>2-3 oatcakes with low fat spft cheese</li>
                    		<li>100g mixed nuts and seeds</li>
                    		<li>Item of fruit</li>
                    		<li>Drink</li>
                    	</ul>
                    	<br>
                    </li>
                    <li><b>1 hour pre-bed:</b>
                    	<ul>
                    		<li>
                    			100g cottege cheese / quark / low fat natural yoghurt<br>
                    			Banana<br>
                    			Small handful of mixed nuts and seeds<br>
                    			Drink
                    		</li>
                    	</ul>
                    	<br>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p>
	                However the plan is merely a general guide, and the portion sizes will need to be adapted to suit 
	                your daily routine. You must eat a variety of different meats/fish, complex carbohydrates, fruit 
	                and vegetables every day, and drink plenty of water.
                </p>
